    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "I personnally don't see OZ as a community of people discussing contract standards. Possibly on the forum, but definitely not here. \r\n\r\nJust this week, there are something like 7 new ERC, not including your, listed on https://weekinethereumnews.com/. Please understand that we need to put filters, and we need these filters to be simple and as unopinionated as possible.\r\n\r\nA a general rule, we are not willing to merge, and commit to provide support, for community contracts that are not strongly backed by either a finalised ERC, or wide adoption. It might be easy for you to write it, it might look like nothing, but understand that if we merge it, we would have to provider support for it for a long time ... and that is not something we take lightly\r\n\r\nAlso, we think \"being part of the OZ library\" would give weight/credibility to a draft ERC, and influence the ERC process. This is something we don't want.\r\n\r\nThat doesn't mean we will never merge this ERC, but there is a workflow for that, and we believe its not yet time for ERC5679.",
